    callClass: 'BROADCAST',
    color: 'var(--broadcast)',
    listenProse: `The <strong>Humpback Whale</strong> produces the longest and most complex songs in the animal kingdom. A single song can last hours. They're sung almost exclusively by males, and every whale in an ocean basin sings the same song — then it slowly evolves over the season. It's cultural transmission.`,
    waveType: 'complex_song',
    freq: { start: 200, end: 800, peak: 400 },
